codex
I found the key logic issue in the verifier: it incorrectly treats `warmupPeriod == 0` as making the finding unexploitable. In this staking contract, `stake(..., claimNow=false)` still creates a warmup position even when the configured warmup is zero, so long as there are at least two overdue epochs the same liability-misaccounting path can still be exercised. I’m rewriting the verifier around that path and funding it with a V2 flashswap as requested.
apply patch
